<article class="node node--type-article node--view-mode-teaser">

    	<div class="teaser-image"><a href="/article/march-2007/deconstruction-katrin?language_content_entity=und" rel="bookmark">

<div class="media media--type-image media--view-mode-teaser">
  
        <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/2015_teaser/public/images/standard/Header_KATRIN.png?itok=Ck98_x-3" width="736" height="414" alt="Photo of spectrometer moving through Karls" />



  </div>




</a></div>
    
  <div class="teaser-date">03/01/07</div>
  <h4 class="teaser-headline">
      <a href="/article/march-2007/deconstruction-katrin?language_content_entity=und" rel="bookmark"><span>KATRIN’s odyssey</span>
</a>
  </h4> 
  <p>People went to great lengths, traveling almost 9000 kilometers over more than 60 days, to deliver an essential, 200-ton component of the KATRIN neutrino experiment.</p>


</article>
